# WordPress integration

## Live state (as of 2026-03-12)

WordPress on dangercreations.com (SiteGround) serves as the identity provider.
JWT Authentication for WP REST API plugin is installed. The JWT secret is shared
between `wp-config.php` (`JWT_AUTH_SECRET_KEY`) and the Tornado container
(`jwt_secret` env var). They must be identical.

### What lives where

| Concern | Location |
|---------|----------|
| JWT plugin config | `wp-config.php` on SiteGround |
| Security filters + shortcode | `kale/functions.php` on SiteGround |
| Setup reference files | `wordpress/dangerfinger-setup/` in this repo |
| JWT validation | `web/auth.py` |
| Auth mixin for handlers | `WpAuthMixin` in `web/server.py` |
| Frontend auth flow | `web/app.js` (handleAuthCallback, initLoginLogout) |
| Configure embed page | `/prosthetics/configure` (WP page ID 1227) |

### Key env vars (Tornado container)

- `jwt_secret` — must match `JWT_AUTH_SECRET_KEY` in wp-config.php exactly
- `wp_auth_url` — `https://dangercreations.com`
- `app_base_url` — the app's own public URL (used for OAuth redirect)

